Note:
Comprehensive tests for the Time module
:End Note

Note: Test basic time operations
:End Note

Let current_time be now
Assert length of current_time is greater than 0

Let timestamp be current timestamp
Assert timestamp is greater than 0

Note: Test sleep functionality
:End Note
Let start_time be current timestamp
Call sleep with seconds as 0.1
Let end_time be current timestamp
Assert end_time is greater than start_time

Note: Test time formatting and parsing
:End Note
Let test_datetime be "2023-12-25 14:30:45"
Let formatted_date be format time as test_datetime with format as "%Y-%m-%d"
Let formatted_time be format time as test_datetime with format as "%H:%M:%S"

Assert formatted_date is equal to "2023-12-25"
Assert formatted_time is equal to "14:30:45"

Let parsed_date be parse time from "2023-12-25" with format as "%Y-%m-%d"
Assert parsed_date contains "2023-12-25"

Note: Test timestamp conversions
:End Note
Let test_ts be 1703520000  Note: 2023-12-25 00:00:00 UTC
Let from_ts be from timestamp test_ts
Assert from_ts contains "2023-12-25"

Let to_ts be to timestamp test_datetime
Assert to_ts is greater than 0

Note: Test time arithmetic - adding time
:End Note
Let base_time be "2023-12-25 14:30:45"

Let add_secs be add 30 seconds to base_time
Let add_mins be add 15 minutes to base_time
Let add_hours be add 2 hours to base_time
Let add_days be add 5 days to base_time
Let add_weeks be add 1 week to base_time
Let add_months be add 1 month to base_time
Let add_years be add 1 year to base_time

Assert add_secs is not equal to base_time
Assert add_mins is not equal to base_time
Assert add_hours is not equal to base_time
Assert add_days is not equal to base_time
Assert add_weeks is not equal to base_time
Assert add_months is not equal to base_time
Assert add_years is not equal to base_time

Note: Test time arithmetic - subtracting time
:End Note
Let sub_secs be subtract 30 seconds from base_time
Let sub_mins be subtract 15 minutes from base_time
Let sub_hours be subtract 2 hours from base_time
Let sub_days be subtract 5 days from base_time
Let sub_weeks be subtract 1 week from base_time
Let sub_months be subtract 1 month from base_time
Let sub_years be subtract 1 year from base_time

Assert sub_secs is not equal to base_time
Assert sub_mins is not equal to base_time
Assert sub_hours is not equal to base_time
Assert sub_days is not equal to base_time
Assert sub_weeks is not equal to base_time
Assert sub_months is not equal to base_time
Assert sub_years is not equal to base_time

Note: Test time differences
:End Note
Let start_dt be "2023-01-01 10:00:00"
Let end_dt be "2023-01-01 15:30:00"

Let diff_secs be difference in seconds between start_dt and end_dt
Let diff_mins be difference in minutes between start_dt and end_dt
Let diff_hours be difference in hours between start_dt and end_dt
Let diff_days be difference in days between start_dt and end_dt

Assert diff_secs is equal to 19800  Note: 5.5 hours in seconds
Assert diff_mins is equal to 330   Note: 5.5 hours in minutes
Assert diff_hours is equal to 5.5
Assert diff_days is equal to 0

Note: Test time comparisons
:End Note
Let dt1 be "2023-01-01"
Let dt2 be "2023-01-15"
Let dt3 be "2023-01-10"

Assert is dt1 before dt2 is equal to true
Assert is dt2 after dt1 is equal to true
Assert is dt1 equal to dt1 is equal to true
Assert is dt3 between dt1 and dt2 is equal to true
Assert is dt1 between dt2 and dt3 is equal to false

Note: Test date component extraction
:End Note
Let test_dt be "2023-12-25 14:30:45"

Let year be year of test_dt
Let month be month of test_dt
Let day be day of test_dt
Let hour be hour of test_dt
Let minute be minute of test_dt
Let second be second of test_dt

Assert year is equal to 2023
Assert month is equal to 12
Assert day is equal to 25
Assert hour is equal to 14
Assert minute is equal to 30
Assert second is equal to 45

Let weekday be weekday of test_dt
Let weekday_name be weekday name of test_dt
Let month_name be month name of test_dt

Assert weekday is greater than or equal to 0
Assert weekday is less than or equal to 6
Assert length of weekday_name is greater than 0
Assert length of month_name is greater than 0

Note: Test date type checks
:End Note
Let weekend_date be "2023-12-23"  Note: Saturday
Let weekday_date be "2023-12-25"  Note: Monday

Assert is weekend weekend_date is equal to true
Assert is weekday weekday_date is equal to true

Note: Test leap year operations
:End Note
Assert is leap year 2024 is equal to true
Assert is leap year 2023 is equal to false
Assert is leap year 2000 is equal to true
Assert is leap year 2100 is equal to false

Let days_in_feb_2024 be days in month of 2024 and 2
Let days_in_feb_2023 be days in month of 2023 and 2

Assert days_in_feb_2024 is equal to 29
Assert days_in_feb_2023 is equal to 28

Let days_in_2024 be days in year 2024
Let days_in_2023 be days in year 2023

Assert days_in_2024 is equal to 366
Assert days_in_2023 is equal to 365

Note: Test week and quarter operations
:End Note
Let test_date be "2023-06-15"
Let week_num be week of year of test_date
Let quarter be quarter of year of test_date

Assert week_num is greater than 0
Assert week_num is less than or equal to 53
Assert quarter is greater than or equal to 1
Assert quarter is less than or equal to 4

Note: Test time boundaries
:End Note
Let test_dt be "2023-12-25 14:30:45"

Let day_start be start of day of test_dt
Let day_end be end of day of test_dt

Assert day_start contains "2023-12-25 00:00:00"
Assert day_end contains "2023-12-25 23:59:59"

Let week_start be start of week of test_dt
Let week_end be end of week of test_dt

Assert length of week_start is greater than 0
Assert length of week_end is greater than 0

Note: Test age calculations
:End Note
Let birth_date be "1990-05-15"
Let current_year be year of now
Let expected_age be current_year minus 1990

Let age be age from birth_date
Assert age is greater than or equal to expected_age minus 1
Assert age is less than or equal to expected_age plus 1

Let is_adult be is adult with birth_date as birth_date and age_limit as 18
Assert is_adult is equal to true

Note: Test business day operations
:End Note
Let start_date be "2023-12-20"  Note: Wednesday
Let end_date be "2023-12-27"    Note: Wednesday

Let business_days be business days between start_date and end_date
Assert business_days is greater than 0

Let next_business be next business day after start_date
Let prev_business be previous business day before end_date

Assert length of next_business is greater than 0
Assert length of prev_business is greater than 0

Assert is business day start_date is equal to true
Assert is business day "2023-12-23" is equal to false  Note: Saturday

Note: Test timezone operations
:End Note
Let local_tz be local timezone
Assert length of local_tz is greater than 0

Let utc_time be current utc time
Assert length of utc_time is greater than 0

Note: Test relative time formatting
:End Note
Let past_time be subtract 2 hours from now
Let future_time be add 3 days to now

Let relative_past be relative time of past_time
Let relative_future be relative time of future_time

Assert length of relative_past is greater than 0
Assert length of relative_future is greater than 0

Note: Test duration operations
:End Note
Let duration_seconds be 3661  Note: 1 hour, 1 minute, 1 second
Let formatted_duration be format duration of duration_seconds

Assert length of formatted_duration is greater than 0

Note: Test date validation
:End Note
Assert is valid date "2023-12-25" is equal to true
Assert is valid date "2023-13-01" is equal to false  Note: Invalid month

Assert is valid time "14:30:45" is equal to true
Assert is valid time "25:00:00" is equal to false  Note: Invalid hour

Assert is valid datetime "2023-12-25 14:30:45" is equal to true
Assert is valid datetime "2023-12-25 25:30:45" is equal to false

Note: Test time utilities
:End Note
Let dt1 be "2023-01-01"
Let dt2 be "2023-12-25"

Let min_dt be minimum datetime of dt1 and dt2
Let max_dt be maximum datetime of dt1 and dt2

Assert min_dt is equal to dt1
Assert max_dt is equal to dt2

Let datetime_list be [dt2, dt1, "2023-06-15"]
Let sorted_list be sort datetimes datetime_list
Let unique_list be unique datetimes datetime_list

Assert length of sorted_list is equal to 3
Assert length of unique_list is equal to 3

Note: Test time ranges
:End Note
Let start be "2023-01-01"
Let end be "2023-01-05"
Let step be "1 day"

Let range_list be datetime range from start to end with step as step
Assert length of range_list is greater than 0

Note: Test error handling
:End Note
Try:
    Let parsed be parse time from "invalid-date" with format as "%Y-%m-%d"
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Note: Expected error for invalid date format
    :End Note

Try:
    Let result be add 1 month to "invalid-date"
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Note: Expected error for invalid date
    :End Note

Note: Test performance with large operations
:End Note
Let start_time be now
Let test_list be []

For each i in range from 1 to 100:
    Let test_date be add i days to start_time
    Add test_date to test_list

Let sorted_test be sort datetimes test_list
Assert length of sorted_test is equal to 100

Call print with message as "All Time module tests passed!" 